:{{see|reticulum}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From later {{L.}} ''[[reticulum]]'', a "[[reticle]]". The meaning is often wrongly interpreted as a "[[net]]", which is an older meaning of the Latin root word.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Reticulum'''

#{{constellation}}: A small [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] [[summer]] sky, said to resemble a [[reticle]]. It lies between the [[constellation]]s of [[Horologium]] and [[Dorado]].

